{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Testing Guide Generator",
  "description": "Automatically reviews recently changed files and generates a comprehensive testing guide including: what was built, step-by-step user testing checklist with expected results, edge cases to test, potential issues to watch for, and any special setup needed. Formats output as a clear, actionable guide for non-technical users.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "agentEnd"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "Review the files that were just modified in this session and provide a comprehensive testing guide with the following sections:\n\n## 1. What Was Built\nSummarize the features, components, or functionality that were added or modified. Be specific about what changed.\n\n## 2. User Testing Checklist\nCreate a clear, step-by-step testing plan that includes:\n- Specific actions to take (numbered steps)\n- Expected results for each action\n- Different scenarios to test (happy path and error cases)\n- Edge cases that should be verified\n\n## 3. Potential Issues to Watch For\nList specific things that might need fixing based on the code changes, including:\n- Common failure points\n- Integration concerns\n- Performance considerations\n- Browser compatibility issues\n\n## 4. Testing Setup & Notes\nDocument any special setup needed:\n- Environment configuration\n- Test data requirements\n- Browser/device recommendations\n- Important context for testing\n\nFormat this as a clear, actionable guide that a non-technical user can follow. Use simple language and be specific about what to click, what to enter, and what should happen."
  }
}